    <note>Shi Shunxian [1470] Zhang Kuo, WJ, 13.17b-18a; Jiangxi TZ, 9.40a. Identified as a Xinzhou, Yongfeng (a county created from Shangrao in 1074) jinshi in Jiangxi TZ, 21.34b, but he has the same generational name as Shidian's [20992] grandfather and associations would be consistent with membership in this lineage. My guess is that there was a move to or from this county and am going to identify Shunxian as a Yushan county resident and as a nephew of Anxing [20989] and cousin of Shunze [20990]. CBD, 2, 1535.</note>
